(NULL, NULL, 'Laptop Stand', 42, 'Marginal — needs a unique angle', NULL, '~€629/mo', FALSE, FALSE, '{"source":"google-sheets-import","original":{"timestamp":"2026-04-25T19:05:22.316Z","input_url":"","source_host":"makerworld.com/en/models/77709","score":"42","verdict":"Marginal — needs a unique angle","title":"Laptop Stand","description":"A minimalist 3D-printed laptop/computer stand featuring embedded M6×3mm magnets for a clean, seamless aesthetic. Designed for desk use with a focus on simplicity and durability.","author":"福气","print_time_ai":"6.2h","material_ai":"~180g PLA (estimated for a multi-plate laptop stand across 3 plates)","downloads":"","likes":"","search_volume":"18000","search_trend":"→ Stable","etsy_listings":"12000","etsy_avg_price":"€24","market_insight":"<b>Laptop stands are a high-search, high-competition category</b> — over 12,000 Etsy listings exist, and most top sellers use wood or aluminium, which buyers perceive as more premium than FDM-printed plastic at comparable price points. <b>3D-printed entries perform best when they offer personalisation (engraved name, logo, adjustable sizing) or a niche fit</b> (e.g. a stand designed specifically for a MacBook Air M3 with cable routing). With a 6.2h print time on a single printer, maximum output is approximately 2 units per day, creating a hard production ceiling that limits monthly revenue potential without multiple machines.","sell_price":"€24.00","units_per_month":"35","gross_revenue":"840","print_cost":"119","etsy_fees":"92","net_profit":"629","manufacturing_verdict":"Works, but has limits","is_3d_optimal":"FALSE","printing_advantage":"Zero tooling cost — allows market testing and rapid design iteration (e.g. custom sizes, cable channels, branding inserts) before committing to any other manufacturing method","etsy_ban_risk":"high","etsy_ban_reason":"The model is licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives 4.0 (CC BY-NC-ND), which explicitly prohibits commercial use —