(NULL, 'https://makerworld.com/models/850834?appSharePlatform=copy', 'Double Barrel Pistol Shotgun - Fidget', 32, 'Don''t sell — weapons compliance risk', NULL, '~€221/mo', FALSE, FALSE, '{"source":"google-sheets-import","original":{"timestamp":"2026-04-25T20:27:15.853Z","input_url":"https://makerworld.com/models/850834?appSharePlatform=copy","source_host":"makerworld.com/models/850834","score":"32","verdict":"Don''t sell — weapons compliance risk","title":"Double Barrel Pistol Shotgun - Fidget","description":"A 3D-printed double-barrelled fidget toy styled as a pistol-shotgun with working hammers, triggers, and a barrel that opens to load decorative shells. Designed as a non-firing anti-stress toy assembled with rubber bands and glue.","author":"Megatiks","print_time_ai":"6.3h","material_ai":"approx. 85g PLA (8 plates at 0.1mm layer height, 15% infill)","downloads":"18.3k","likes":"","search_volume":"1200","search_trend":"down 18% YoY","etsy_listings":"320","etsy_avg_price":"€19","market_insight":"<b>Demand for fidget toys has contracted significantly since the 2022–2023 peak</b>, and weapon-styled fidgets occupy a legally ambiguous subcategory that Etsy, PayPal, and Stripe have all flagged in their prohibited items policies at various times. <b>Buyer perception is a compounding problem</b>: the realistic gun aesthetic will deter the 58% female Etsy audience and the large US gift-buyer segment, while the plastic FDM finish at this price point struggles to justify the cost versus cheap injection-moulded alternatives from AliExpress. <b>Production is also constrained</b> — 8 plates at 6.3h total and a glue-assembly step means roughly 2 units per day on a single printer, and the matte grey or black PLA finish is notoriously difficult to photograph in a way that communicates the mechanical detail that makes the product interesting.","sell_price":"€19.00","units_per_month":"20","gross_revenue":"380","print_cost":"54","etsy_fees":"38","net_profit":"221","manufacturing_ve