(NULL, 'https://makerworld.com/models/115260?appSharePlatform=copy', 'Date Keeper Perpetual Flip Calendar', 62, 'Good for the right audience', NULL, '~€166/mo', FALSE, FALSE, '{"source":"google-sheets-import","original":{"timestamp":"2026-04-27T05:51:14.015Z","input_url":"https://makerworld.com/models/115260?appSharePlatform=copy","source_host":"makerworld.com/models/115260","score":"62","verdict":"Good for the right audience","title":"Date Keeper Perpetual Flip Calendar","description":"A fully 3D printed perpetual flip calendar requiring no hardware — no magnets, bolts, glue, or screws. Designed for desk or office display with multi-colour tile support via AMS or manual painting.","author":"make 3D","print_time_ai":"10.5h","material_ai":"~180g PLA (estimated across 5 plates at 15% infill)","downloads":"14.3k","likes":"14300","search_volume":"9500","search_trend":"→ Stable","etsy_listings":"1800","etsy_avg_price":"€26","market_insight":"<b>Demand for perpetual and flip calendars on Etsy is real but moderate</b> — it is not a saturated category like phone holders, but competition from laser-cut wood versions is strong and those sell at similar price points with a premium handcrafted perception. <b>Buyers in this category skew toward home-office gifters</b> (especially around New Year, housewarmings, and back-to-school), meaning there is a seasonal spike in Q4 and early January that a new seller could target. At 10.5 hours per print, a single printer will produce only ~1 unit per day, making stock build-up slow and production the primary bottleneck for a new seller.","sell_price":"€26.00","units_per_month":"12","gross_revenue":"312","print_cost":"113","etsy_fees":"33","net_profit":"166","manufacturing_verdict":"Works, but has limits","is_3d_optimal":"TRUE","printing_advantage":"Zero tooling — the snap-fit multi-part mechanism with variable-width housings would require complex multi-cavity injection mould tooling at tens of thousands of euros, making 3D printing the on