(NULL, 'https://makerworld.com/en/crowdfunding/72-leah-a-design-concept-in-light-and-form', 'LEAH – Modular 3D Printed Lighting System', 72, 'Good for the right audience', NULL, '~€1604/mo', FALSE, FALSE, '{"source":"google-sheets-import","original":{"timestamp":"2026-05-05T03:09:13.280Z","input_url":"https://makerworld.com/en/crowdfunding/72-leah-a-design-concept-in-light-and-form","source_host":"makerworld.com/en/crowdfunding/72-leah-a-design-concept-in-light-and-form","score":"72","verdict":"Good for the right audience","title":"LEAH – Modular 3D Printed Lighting System","description":"LEAH is a modular lamp collection with 20 bases and 25 shades offering 500 combinations, connected via a precision bayonet mechanism and compatible with E14, E27, and Bambu Lab LED kits. Designed under the FORMAstudios label, it prints support-free and AMS-free on any FDM printer including the A1 mini.","author":"3dwb","print_time_ai":"Estimated 4–8h per component (full lamp assembly likely 8–14h total)","material_ai":"Estimated 150–250g PLA per full assembly","downloads":"","likes":"","search_volume":"9400","search_trend":"↑ 18% YoY","etsy_listings":"4200","etsy_avg_price":"€78","market_insight":"<b>Demand for unique 3D printed lighting on Etsy is real and growing</b>, with buyers actively searching for designer table lamps, geometric shades, and modular lighting in the €60–€150 band. Competition is moderate rather than saturated — unlike generic planters or cable clips, handcrafted lamp designs with a clear brand story face far fewer identical listings. <b>Buyer perception is a critical factor</b>: photography quality, lifestyle staging, and brand credibility determine conversion far more than in functional product categories. The long print time per unit is the primary production constraint — a single printer realistically yields one full lamp per day, capping monthly output at roughly 20–25 units before accounting for failures and fulfilment time.","sell_price":"€95.00","units_per_month":"20","gross_revenue":"1900","print_cost":"106","etsy_fees":"190","net_profit":"1604","manufacturing_verdict":"Ideal method","is_3d_optimal":"TRUE","printing_advantage":"Modular geometry — the bayonet connector system and organic shade profiles create infinite combinations that injection moulding cannot produce without separate costly tooling for every variant.","etsy_ban_risk":"low","etsy_ban_reason":"The LEAH crowdfunding campaign explicitly offers a Commercial License tier granting lifetime rights to sell physical prints — if the seller has backed this tier and holds that license, Etsy reselling is permitted under March","legal_risk":"","legal_desc":"","copyright_risk":"","copyright_desc":"","best_platform":"","category":"decor","marketplace":"","price_range":"","print_time_input":"","material_input":"","seller_goal":"business","printer_count":"","printer_type":"","experience":"","weekly_time":"","active_markets":"","social_media":"","sell_from":"","sell_to":"WORLDWIDE","legal_flags":""}}'::jsonb, NULL, '2026-05-05T03:09:13.280Z'),
(NULL, 'https://makerworld.com/en/models/2659800-worby-wall-organizer-with-red-blue-and-yellow#profileId-2941918', 'WORBY - Wall Organizer with Red, Blue, and Yellow', 72, 'Good for the right audience', NULL, '~€291/mo', FALSE, FALSE, '{"source":"google-sheets-import","original":{"timestamp":"2026-05-05T03:11:38.806Z","input_url":"https://makerworld.com/en/models/2659800-worby-wall-organizer-with-red-blue-and-yellow#profileId-2941918","source_host":"makerworld.com/en/models/2659800-worby-wall-organizer-with-red-blue-and-yellow","score":"72","verdict":"Good for the right audience","title":"WORBY - Wall Organizer with Red, Blue, and Yellow","description":"A modular, neoplasticism-inspired wall organizer system where coloured panels and functional modules (hooks, bins, shelves) click into a magnetic base grid, turning everyday clutter into wall art. Designed by Scott Yu-Jan, it is fully scalable and customisable via an online configurator.","author":"Scott Yu-Jan","print_time_ai":"8.2h (base grid plate set; full system across all profiles totals 30+ hours)","material_ai":"Multi-colour PLA Matte (Red, Blue, Yellow, White, Charcoal) — estimated 350–500g total for a starter set at ~€0.025/g","downloads":"","likes":"4200","search_volume":"9400","search_trend":"↑ 18% YoY","etsy_listings":"12000","etsy_avg_price":"€22","market_insight":"<b>Demand for aesthetically distinctive wall organizers is strong</b> — the Mondrian/neoplasticism angle is genuinely rare on Etsy and provides a visual hook that commodity organizers cannot match, giving meaningful differentiation in a high-competition category. <b>Buyer perception of 3D-printed decor is positive when the colour palette is deliberate and the finish is clean</b> — PLA Matte filaments closely mimic painted surfaces, which is a strong fit here. The multi-profile nature of the system means each listing can be tiered (base grid only, starter kit, full bundle), allowing upsell and repeat purchase from the same buyer — but <b>total