(NULL, 'https://makerworld.com/it/models/1283460-mending-loom?from=search#profileId-1312066', 'Mending Loom / Darning Loom', 52, 'Marginal — needs a unique angle', NULL, '~€1823/mo', FALSE, FALSE, '{"source":"google-sheets-import","original":{"timestamp":"2026-05-05T09:42:37.880Z","input_url":"https://makerworld.com/it/models/1283460-mending-loom?from=search#profileId-1312066","source_host":"makerworld.com/it/models/1283460-mending-loom","score":"52","verdict":"Marginal — needs a unique angle","title":"Mending Loom / Darning Loom","description":"A compact 3D-printed mending loom with 14 movable needles designed to repair clothes or weave decorative patches. Prints in a single plate at 65g filament with minimal supports, requiring only 2 screws and 2 rubber bands to assemble.","author":"Tigerstern","print_time_ai":"2.5h","material_ai":"65g PLA (PETG recommended for needles)","downloads":"","likes":"","search_volume":"3200","search_trend":"↑ 18% YoY","etsy_listings":"420","etsy_avg_price":"€24","market_insight":"<b>Demand is real but niche:</b> the visible mending and sustainable fashion movement drives genuine Etsy search traffic for darning looms, but total monthly search volume is modest (~3,000) compared to mainstream craft tools. <b>Competition is low-to-moderate</b> (~420 listings) and most existing sellers price between €18–€45, leaving room for a well-photographed, story-driven listing. Buyer perception of 3D-printed functional craft tools is generally positive when positioned as ''handmade in small batches'' — layer lines are acceptable here as this is a utilitarian sewing tool, not a decorative item. <b>Production is comfortable on a single printer</b> at 2.5h per unit, but the €30–€60 target price range is at the high end for this category and will require strong differentiation.","sell_price":"€39.00","units_per_month":"55","gross_revenue":"2145","print_cost":"108","etsy_fees":"214","net_profit":"1823","manufacturing_verdict":"Works, but has limits","is_3d_optimal":"TRUE","printing_advantage":"Zero tooling — the integrated 14-needle movable head geometry is impractical to injection-mould at craft-market volumes, and small-batch production fits Etsy''s handmade positioning perfectly","etsy_ban_risk":"medium","etsy_ban_reason":"The file is hosted on MakerWorld as a free download but no explicit commercial or print-for-sale license is","legal_risk":"","legal_desc":"","copyright_risk":"","copyright_desc":"","best_platform":"","category":"functional","marketplace":"","price_range":"30-60","print_time_input":"","material_input":"","seller_goal":"business","printer_count":"","printer_type":"","experience":"","weekly_time":"","active_markets":"","social_media":"","sell_from":"","sell_to":"WORLDWIDE","legal_flags":"none"}}'::jsonb, NULL, '2026-05-05T09:42:37.880Z'),
(NULL, 'https://makerworld.com/en/models/2504163-gridfinity-case-system#profileId-2828010', 'Gridfinity Case System (5x4 Rugged Stackable)', 52, 'Marginal — needs a unique angle', NULL, '~€235/mo', FALSE, FALSE, '{"source":"google-sheets-import","original":{"timestamp":"2026-05-05T13:04:57.625Z","input_url":"https://makerworld.com/en/models/2504163-gridfinity-case-system#profileId-2828010","source_host":"makerworld.com/en/models/2504163-gridfinity-case-system","score":"52","verdict":"Marginal — needs a unique angle","title":"Gridfinity Case System (5x4 Rugged Stackable)","description":"A rugged, stackable Gridfinity-spec case system with dual latches, reinforced hinges, optional TPU gasket seal, and full stackability — designed for a fixed 5x4 footprint with 6U or 7U height bins. Requires M3 screws and approximately 23.5h to print across 7 plates.","author":"pixelwave","print_time_ai":"23.5h (7 plates)","material_ai":"~450–550g PLA (estimated for full case set at scale)","downloads":"","likes":"","search_volume":"3200","search_trend":"↑ 18% YoY","etsy_listings":"1800","etsy_avg_price":"€32","market_insight":"<b>Gridfinity is a passionate maker community standard</b>, but that community is almost entirely self-printing — the commercial buyer pool is much smaller than maker engagement suggests. <b>Etsy buyers in the tool-storage category are practical and price-anchored</b>: a full case system at €35–45 competes directly with off-shelf plastic cases from B&Q, Amazon, and Sortimo. The 23.5h print time on a single printer caps output at roughly 12–16 units per month, and at €35 sell price the hourly return is marginal; <b>offering customisation (label inserts, colour combos, branded lids for tradespeople) is the lever that breaks price resistance</b> and justifies a premium over commodity storage.","sell_price":"€34.00","units_per_month":"14","gross_revenue":"476","print_cost":"191","etsy_fees":"50","net_profit":"235","manufacturing_verdict":"Works, but has limits","is_3d_optimal":"TRUE","printing_advantage":"Zero tooling — the integrated hinge bosses, dual-latch recesses, and Gridfinity stackable profile are impossible to injection-mould economically at hobby volumes, making FDM the only viable production route without a five-figure mould investment.","etsy_ban_risk":"medium","etsy_ban_reason":"The MakerWorld page","legal_risk":"","legal_desc":"","copyright_risk":"","copyright_desc":"","best_platform":"","category":"functional","marketplace":"etsy","price_range":"","print_time_input":"","material_input":"","seller_goal":"business","printer_count":"","printer_type":"","experience":"some","weekly_time":"","active_markets":"","social_media":"","sell_from":"","sell_to":"WORLDWIDE","legal_flags":""}}'::jsonb, NULL, '2026-05-05T13:04:57.625Z'),
(NULL, 'https://makerworld.com/en/models/2504163-gridfinity-case-system#profileId-2828010', 'Gridfinity Case System (5x4)', 52, 'Marginal — needs a unique angle', NULL, '~€226/mo', FALSE, FALSE, '{"source":"google-sheets-import","original":{"timestamp":"2026-05-05T13:17:58.933Z","input_url":"https://makerworld.com/en/models/2504163-gridfinity-case-system#profileId-2828010","source_host":"makerworld.com/en/models/2504163-gridfinity-case-system","score":"52","verdict":"Marginal — needs a unique angle","title":"Gridfinity Case System (5x4)","description":"A rugged, stackable Gridfinity-spec case system with dual latches, reinforced hinges, optional TPU gasket sealing, and full stackability. Designed for a fixed 5x4 footprint with 6U/7U height compatibility.","author":"pixelwave","print_time_ai":"23.5h (full set, 7 plates)","material_ai":"~400–600g PLA estimated (large multi-part case system)","downloads":"","likes":"","search_volume":"2800","search_trend":"↑ 18% YoY","etsy_listings":"420","etsy_avg_price":"€24","market_insight":"<b>Gridfinity is a growing niche</b> with strong community interest, but the majority of buyers are themselves makers who already own printers — the addressable commercial market on Etsy is relatively thin. <b>Competition is moderate</b> (~420 Etsy listings) but most listings are for individual bins, not full case systems, so the case format has differentiation potential. <b>The 23.5h print time is the primary production constraint</b> — at a side-hustle pace with a single printer, realistic output is no more than 20–22 units per month after accounting for failures and bed changes.","sell_price":"€24.00","units_per_month":"18","gross_revenue":"432","print_cost":"159","etsy_fees":"47","net_profit":"226","manufacturing_verdict":"Works, but has limits","is_3d_optimal":"TRUE","printing_advantage":"Zero tooling — the interlocking Gridfinity-spec geometry, integrated hinge bosses, and dual-latch recesses are impossible to injection-mould economically